---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailSignup from '../components/EmailSignup.astro';
import Chart from '../components/Chart.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="PowerEurope | Europe Must Build Again">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative bg-gradient-to-b from-primary-950 to-primary-900 text-white py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="container-wide text-center">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold mb-6 tracking-tight">
        Europe Must Build Again
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-primary-200 mb-4 font-medium">
        Not left. Not right. Forward.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-primary-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Cheap energy is the foundation of everything—jobs, defense, AI, and yes, environmental protection. Without power, Europe has no future.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/join" class="btn btn-accent text-lg px-8 py-4">
          Join the Movement
        </a>
        <a href="/data" class="btn bg-white/10 text-white hover:bg-white/20 text-lg px-8 py-4">
          See the Data
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Abstract power/energy pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden pointer-events-none opacity-10">
      <svg class="absolute -right-1/4 -top-1/4 w-1/2 h-auto" viewBox="0 0 400 400" fill="none">
        <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="150" stroke="white" stroke-width="1"/>
        <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="100" stroke="white" stroke-width="1"/>
        <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="50" stroke="white" stroke-width="1"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Problem -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
        Wealth Protects the Environment. Poverty Does Not.
      </h2>

      <div class="prose text-lg">
        <p>We were told that expensive energy was the price of a green future.</p>
        <p><strong>We were wrong.</strong></p>
        <p>
          The countries that protect their forests, clean their rivers, and invest in new technology
          are wealthy countries. Poor countries strip their land, burn what they have, and survive.
        </p>
        <p>
          Europe is choosing decline. Decade after decade of high energy costs will not make us green.
          It will make us poor. And poor Europe will not protect anything.
        </p>
        <p>
          China burns coal today to fund nuclear tomorrow. America uses cheap gas to power AI dominance.
          Europe taxes itself and calls it virtue.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our factories close. Our industries leave. Our young emigrate. And we lecture the world about
          climate while importing everything from countries with no standards at all.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
          This is not environmentalism. This is suicide with good intentions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Stakes: Energy Chart -->
  <section class="section bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">
        AI Is the Industrial Revolution of Our Time
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">
        Within ten years, artificial intelligence will reshape every industry, every military, every economy.
        Training a single frontier AI model already costs billions. Most of that is energy.
      </p>

      <!-- Energy price divergence chart -->
      <Chart
        id="energy-divergence-hero"
        title="Industrial Electricity Prices: Europe vs. Competitors"
        caption="Europe pays 2-3x more for industrial electricity than the US or China. This gap is widening."
        height="450px"
      />

      <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center">
        <div class="p-6">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-emerald-600 mb-2">United States</div>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Cheap gas, growing nuclear, light regulation. <strong>Building AI.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">China</div>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Massive nuclear expansion, state-controlled prices. <strong>Building AI.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary-600 mb-2">Europe</div>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Most expensive electricity in the developed world. <strong>Regulating AI.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-lg text-gray-700 mt-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Without cheap energy, Europe cannot build sovereign AI. We will rent it. From America. From China.
        We will be users, not creators. Customers, not powers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Plan -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">
        The Plan: Energy Sovereignty in 15 Years
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
        We are not ideologues. We are engineers, economists, citizens who can read a chart. Here is what works.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Immediate -->
        <div class="bg-amber-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-amber-200">
          <div class="text-sm font-bold text-amber-700 mb-2">IMMEDIATE</div>
          <div class="text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Now – 2027</div>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600">→</span>
              Suspend carbon taxes and emissions trading schemes
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600">→</span>
              Reopen coal plants as bridge capacity
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600">→</span>
              Emergency restart of all closable nuclear facilities
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600">→</span>
              Wartime regulatory framework—no more decade-long approvals
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Medium-term -->
        <div class="bg-primary-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-primary-200">
          <div class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">MEDIUM-TERM</div>
          <div class="text-lg font-semibold mb-1">2027 – 2032</div>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-primary-600">→</span>
              Massive grid expansion—current infrastructure cannot handle growth
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-primary-600">→</span>
              License proven reactor designs from Korea and the US
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-primary-600">→</span>
              Deploy small modular reactors at scale
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-primary-600">→</span>
              Build domestic uranium enrichment—end dependence on Russia
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Long-term -->
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-emerald-200">
          <div class="text-sm font-bold text-emerald-700 mb-2">LONG-TERM</div>
          <div class="text-lg font-semibold mb-1">2032 – 2040</div>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-emerald-600">→</span>
              New nuclear fleet online across the continent
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-emerald-600">→</span>
              Coal phases out as baseload is secured
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-emerald-600">→</span>
              Energy cost parity with US and China
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-emerald-600">→</span>
              European AI infrastructure powered by clean, cheap, abundant electricity
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-xl font-semibold mt-12 text-gray-900">
        Coal is the bridge. Nuclear is the destination. Denial is the cliff.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Politics -->
  <section class="section bg-gray-900 text-white">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">
        This Is Not Left vs Right
      </h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert mx-auto">
        <p class="text-gray-300">We know the objections.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-300">The right says: "The EU cannot be trusted with this."</p>
        <p class="text-gray-300">The left says: "Nuclear is dangerous, coal is immoral."</p>
        <p class="text-xl text-white font-semibold">We say: "Your grandchildren don't care about your party."</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-12">
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">To the Right</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            You want sovereignty? It requires energy. You want industry? It requires energy.
            You want defense? It requires energy. <strong class="text-white">Help us build.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">To the Left</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            You want to protect the climate? Wealth enables that. Poverty does not.
            You want to protect democracy? It requires a Europe that can defend itself.
            <strong class="text-white">Help us build.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-lg text-gray-300 mt-12">
        The environmental movement was captured by people who prefer decline to construction.
        That is not environmentalism. That is a death cult with good aesthetics.
      </p>
      <p class="text-center text-xl text-white font-semibold mt-6">
        We welcome everyone who wants Europe to matter. Left, right, center.
        Nationalist, federalist. Old, young. One goal. Every European.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Now -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
        The Window Is Closing
      </h2>

      <div class="prose text-lg">
        <p>Every year we wait:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>Energy gap widens</li>
          <li>More factories leave</li>
          <li>More talent emigrates</li>
          <li>AI leadership consolidates elsewhere</li>
          <li>Our leverage shrinks</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8">
          There is no scenario where Europe remains relevant while paying three times what competitors pay for electricity.
        </p>
        <p>
          There is no scenario where we build sovereign AI without the power to run it.
        </p>
        <p>
          There is no scenario where we defend ourselves without an industrial base to arm ourselves.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
          The next ten years will determine whether Europe is a power or a peninsula.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- History -->
  <section class="section bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
        We Have Done This Before
      </h2>

      <div class="prose text-lg">
        <p>
          In 1945, Europe was rubble. Destroyed. Defeated.
        </p>
        <p>
          Within thirty years, we built the most prosperous, peaceful civilization in human history.
        </p>
        <p>
          We built nuclear plants. We built industries. We built institutions.
        </p>
        <p>
          We did it because we chose to. Because the generation before us understood that survival
          requires building, not managing decline.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
          We bear the scars of fascism. We know what weakness invites. We know what happens when
          democracies cannot defend themselves.
        </p>
        <p>
          Europe should be a beacon to the world. A proof that freedom and prosperity and dignity can coexist.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
          But beacons require power.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Join -->
  <section class="section bg-primary-900 text-white">
    <div class="container-narrow text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">
        What Can You Do?
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12 text-left">
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Share This</h3>
          <p class="text-primary-200 text-sm">
            The message spreads when you spread it. Talk to friends, post on social media.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Contact Your Representatives</h3>
          <p class="text-primary-200 text-sm">
            Demand they take a position on energy sovereignty. Make it an issue they cannot ignore.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Fund the Movement</h3>
          <p class="text-primary-200 text-sm">
            We are citizen-funded. No party, no corporation, no government. Your support matters.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 text-gray-900">
        <EmailSignup variant="hero" heading="Join the Movement" subheading="Get updates on European energy policy and campaign progress." />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  // Energy price divergence chart
  import * as Plot from '@observablehq/plot';

  const data = [
    // Europe (EU average industrial prices €/MWh)
    { year: 2010, region: 'Europe', price: 95 },
    { year: 2012, region: 'Europe', price: 105 },
    { year: 2014, region: 'Europe', price: 112 },
    { year: 2016, region: 'Europe', price: 98 },
    { year: 2018, region: 'Europe', price: 110 },
    { year: 2020, region: 'Europe', price: 95 },
    { year: 2022, region: 'Europe', price: 180 },
    { year: 2024, region: 'Europe', price: 145 },
    // United States
    { year: 2010, region: 'United States', price: 55 },
    { year: 2012, region: 'United States', price: 50 },
    { year: 2014, region: 'United States', price: 52 },
    { year: 2016, region: 'United States', price: 48 },
    { year: 2018, region: 'United States', price: 50 },
    { year: 2020, region: 'United States', price: 45 },
    { year: 2022, region: 'United States', price: 65 },
    { year: 2024, region: 'United States', price: 58 },
    // China
    { year: 2010, region: 'China', price: 60 },
    { year: 2012, region: 'China', price: 62 },
    { year: 2014, region: 'China', price: 65 },
    { year: 2016, region: 'China', price: 58 },
    { year: 2018, region: 'China', price: 60 },
    { year: 2020, region: 'China', price: 55 },
    { year: 2022, region: 'China', price: 70 },
    { year: 2024, region: 'China', price: 62 },
  ];

  const container = document.getElementById('energy-divergence-hero');
  if (container) {
    container.innerHTML = '';
    const chart = Plot.plot({
      width: container.clientWidth,
      height: 400,
      marginLeft: 60,
      marginRight: 100,
      marginBottom: 40,
      style: {
        background: 'transparent',
        fontSize: '12px',
      },
      x: {
        label: 'Year',
        tickFormat: 'd',
      },
      y: {
        label: '€/MWh',
        grid: true,
      },
      color: {
        domain: ['Europe', 'United States', 'China'],
        range: ['#1d4ed8', '#16a34a', '#dc2626'],
      },
      marks: [
        Plot.line(data, {
          x: 'year',
          y: 'price',
          stroke: 'region',
          strokeWidth: 3,
        }),
        Plot.dot(data, {
          x: 'year',
          y: 'price',
          fill: 'region',
          r: 4,
        }),
        Plot.text(
          data.filter(d => d.year === 2024),
          {
            x: 'year',
            y: 'price',
            text: 'region',
            dx: 10,
            textAnchor: 'start',
            fill: 'region',
            fontWeight: 'bold',
          }
        ),
      ],
    });
    container.appendChild(chart);
  }
</script>
